social_posts.post_text:
Took a road trip home to DC from NYC in the new 2023 @NissanUSA Versa SR. This attractive, compact sedan and all of its safety features got me home for the Thanksgiving holiday safe and sound.

Stylish, with comfy seats and all the modern tech, the 2023 Nissan Versa SR is surprisingly spacious. I actually packed up the car with my winter clothes and some other things I needed to bring back to NYC and had lots of space left.

Affordable, practical and exceptional gas mileage, if you’re looking for a competent sedan that’s economical the Versa may be for you!

Thanks to my friends at @Nissan for the ride home! 

#NissanVersa #RoadTrip

Never thought I wanted to be a magician but I get to make magic ✨ each day on @SherriShowTV with @SherriEShepherd.
 
No. 1 new show in daytime!

No. 2 overall in the key demographic! 

And an unofficial stat: No. 1 place for Laughter, Joy & Feel-Good Fun on daytime!

Thank You to the guests who have contributed to the magic! 🙏🏽 

#SherriShowTV #ExecutiveProducer

DEVASTATED by the death of my friend Stephen "TWITCH" Boss! 💔 Truly gutted by this news.

@sir_twitch_alot was a genuinely good guy. We initially met on the set of @willpowerpacker's film "Stomp The Yard 2: Homecoming" and then kept in touch throughout the years. 

More recently, Twitch kept checking in and encouraging me during my Executive Producer negotiations at @SherriShowTV.  I respected him so much for that because my journey with @SherriEShepherd was happening around the same time his journey with Ellen DeGeneres was ending.

A few weeks ago, Twitch was listening to an interview I did with @RushionMcDonald on his show Money Making Conversations Show where I celebrated Twitch for his support on my E.P. journey and he reached out to thank me for it. 

My prayers for his wife @allisonholker and his entire family! 🙏🏽 

Please, please check on the folks you love! You never know what they are dealing with... especially during this time of year! #Twitch

Santa Claus 🎅🏾 sent some amazing people to the @SherriShowTV for our holiday shows. 

‘Tis the season’ to be surrounded by awesome guests; work alongside a great production team; and help @SherriEShepherd give the gift of a ‘Good Time’ to the audience. 🎁🎄

#SherriShowTV #ExecutiveProducer

(Some 📸’s by @andrewwerner)

“Ain’t No Mo” on Broadway is hilarious, thought-provoking, audacious and truly compelling! The play is well-written and features - in my humble opinion - some performances that are worthy of Tony nominations! 

Unfortunately, this incredible work by @jordanecooper and produced by @leedaniels is ending prematurely.

I’m glad we were able to have to them come to @SherriShowTV and discuss Jordan’s historic Broadway breakthrough.

Seeing the show a second time was even greater than the first. I ran into some old friends and made some new ones.

If they tour #AintNoMo please see go see it! Kudos to the cast on a job well done! 🎭 #SaveAintNoMo

Whether reconnecting with friends, making new ones or just vibing with people while out in these streets; I had some really cool encounters this year! 

This is my 2022 Year-End Photo Dump part one! 📸
#PhotoDump

What a year! Good vibes, hard work, fun encounters and a lot of life lived! Thanks to everyone that contributed to the memories. 

This is my 2022 Year-End Photo Dump part two! 📸
#PhotoDump 

(Some @sherrishowtv photos by @andrewwerner)

Trailblazing journalist Barbara Walters has passed at age 93.

“I like your way with words!” - is what the legendary Barbara Walters said to me on April 22, 2014 when I guest co-hosted @TheView.

She celebrated me on live TV and it shifted how many in the industry viewed me! 

I was so grateful to work with this living legend two weeks before she retired. 

A career unmatched and a life well lived.

Truly iconic. 🙏🏽

#BarbaraWalters

God is Good! 🙏🏽

Thanks to everyone that has watched, been supportive & encouraged @sherrieshepherd & I on this journey to bring a ‘good time’ to daytime!

Two more seasons of @sherrishowtv coming! 🙌🏽

I thought I was just going to a social event, never expected it to also feed my soul! 

Thanks to @candicartertv @kendisgibson & @cameronedwardjones for creating this party with a purpose and bringing us all together!

(Swipe ⬅️ for more 📸’s)

Those that know me well know that I’m not an overtly emotional person & I hate crying in public! I know that stands against everything @KingJayBarnett is doing to eradicate toxic masculinity; but it’s something I still struggle with.

The generosity of @SherriEShepherd to take her moment to honor me made my attempts to fight back these tears a losing battle! For her to acknowledge the sacrifices I’ve made to go on this journey with her… it just honestly wiped me out!

To find someone as authentic, compassionate, loving & God-led as Sherri in Hollywood is sometimes rare. I’m so blessed that God allowed our worlds to collide, our friendship to sustain over 20 years and for us to be in partnership to bring joy, laughter and inspiration into the homes of viewers on a daily basis.

Thank you Sherri for being YOU! 

And Thank you to everyone for the encouragement & well-wishes on our two-season renewal + those that pushed me to post this clip! #SherriShowTV

The St. Jude Celebration of Hope: Homecoming 2023 weekend in Memphis was such a vibe. People from every facet of the entertainment industry came together to raise awareness for the children’s research hospital. 

So good seeing friends, colleagues and meeting new people; all while being educated and inspired by the incredible work that happens at St. Jude.

(Swipe ⬅️ for more 📸)

Please join me and get your #ThisShirtSavesLives t-shirt at MusicGives.org 

#MusicGives #COH2023 

First Photo by: @KatieKauss

social_posts.post_text:
Not only has @SherriShowTV been picked up for two seasons & nominated for Outstanding Talk Series by @NAACPImageAwards; but we had a January full of great guests and experts that helped bring our feel-good experience to life each day!

Thank You for watching, supporting and all the wonderful feedback! #SherriShowTV

(Swipe ⬅️ for more 📸’s)

Boy, we been having a time at @SherriShowTV! 

As @Luenell likes to say, it’s the “happiest place on daytime!”

Thanks to everyone that has contributed to giving our audience a ‘good time!’ #SherriShowTV

(📸’s by @debrillantoine & @kristenayanah)

Hi! I’m Jawn Murray and I just won at the @NAACPImageAwards for Outstanding Talk Series for Executive Producing @SherriShowTV hosted by @SherriEShepherd!

God Is Good! 🙏🏽 #NAACPImageAwards

Last night, @SherriShowTV won for Outstanding Talk Show for @NAACPImageAwards! To say @sherrieshepherd & I were blown away is an understatement! 

Thank You to the @NAACP & everyone that voted for us. Thanks to our syndication company Debmar-Mercury & parent company @Lionsgate. 

Maybe I’ve watched too many repeats of “Sanford & Son” throughout the years because I clutched my chest just like Fred Sanford! 

True Story: Our producers & team had to put up with me saying I wanted to meet “Bel-Air” star @CoCoJones and singing her song “ICU” all day. You’ll see in this video I am telling her “I been singing your song all day…” and after the speech, “when are you coming on our show?” And shoutout to @armaniblanco for also presenting our category. 

Having some of our producers there with us - @the1fwynn @marcoglorious @imjustpatrick_ & @ashleyy_andreaa - made this even more special.

Thanks @kymwhitley for capturing this video! 

God Is Good! 🙏🏽

#NAACPImageAwards

The NAACP Image Award-winning @SherriShowTV just celebrated its 100th episode. Where did the time go?

What a privilege being on this journey with @sherrieshepherd & a big THANK YOU to all of the amazing guests that have contributed to giving our viewers a ‘good-time!’

#SherriShowTV #Creed3

(📸’s by @andrewwerner & @Kristenayanah)

#ICYMI - A FEEL GOOD TIME! #Throwback to the Norfolk State University Dancers and their legendary routine to our theme song! Submit YOUR video showing us how you’re having a “Feel Good Time” to our SHERRI show theme song. GET INFO NOW at sherrishowtv.com/be-on-the-show/feel-good-time-dance 

#sherri #sherrishowtv #sherrishepherd #fun #joy #laughter #daytimetv #talkshow

From icons like @therealmaryjblige to blasts from the past like @thekikishepard or hilarious comics like @sherylunderwood; we have such a wide variety of guests on @SherriShowTV. 

From authors to intellects and the occasional Real Housewife, THANKS to every guest that has joined us for a ‘good time!’ #SherriShowTV

The good folks at @Starz invited me to a private dinner with the cast of @GhostStarz.

The intimate night was hosted by @TamronHall & Starz curated a group of VIP’s & media personalities that came together to toast the launch of season three.

Always a good time chopping it up with @methodmanofficial, I laughed so much sitting next to @michaelraineyjr & so dope finally meeting @larenztate. 

Great Night, Excellent Cast! #PowerGhost

How’s your week going? Mine? Well, @SherriEShepherd & I spent ours hanging with my favorite male group of all time @NewEdition!

Thank You @realjohnnygill22 @therealralphtresvant @bigrondevoe @mrrickybell @617MikeBiv & @KingBobbyBrown for bringing the “legendary on @SherriShowTV” to life for us! #NE4Life 

📸’s by @andrewwerner 

🤠 by @madebyrodneyjon

The incomparable @TheeBillyPorter is a special person. He’s Hollywood A-List. A multi-hyphenate megastar. And yet, he took time in this appearance on @SherriShowTV to talk about the impact that I had on him.

It was humbling. I am grateful. And his gratitude means more to me than he knows.

The truth is, I’ve helped a lot of people throughout the years. Connection is my superpower! And while I’ve done things to completely shift the professional trajectory of folks who have never said Thank You, Billy was impacted by just my genuine kindness.

May this moment inspire us all! 🙏🏽

#SherriShowTV #BillyPorter

In 1999, while interning at @WPGC in DC, a vocal powerhouse who was the lead singer of an iconic girl group named @officialSWV became my friend! That’s right, @therealCOKOswv was my Day 1️⃣!

In 2005, @phillionaire1911 called and asked if I thought we could get SWV back together (full story in the 2nd slide)…

Now in 2023, SWV came to NYC to promote their new @BravoTV series “SWV & Xscape: The Queens of R&B” on the show I executive produce, @SherriShowTV.

We’ve all come a long way… so much to be proud of! 🖤

#TheQueensOfRB #SWVXscape #SherriShowTV

(📸’s 1 & 3 by @andrewwerner)

Needed a quick getaway while on spring hiatus at @SherriShowTV and went to Nashville to see @NewEdition’s Legacy Tour!

Saw the living legend Dr. Bobby Jones backstage, and met both @CarrieUnderwood and @MrsSole while at the show.

Got to spend some time with my friend @mdoolittle; and then some really dope people came together to celebrate the birthday of the one and only @phillionaire1911! 

I so appreciate you @TresaSanders - thanks for everything! And thanks for hanging out with me @ChefJamika!

When I left Music City, I looked like I had a good time! 

#Nashville #NewEdition

HAPPY BIRTHDAY to ME!

Spoke on a panel at @NorfolkStateUniversity on Thursday night & afterwards took a moment to sit on the steps of the building I was in to reflect on how so much that I dreamed of doing while a student there has actually come to pass.

This year on my birthday; I am grateful for my journey; truly thankful for another year of life, feel blessed to have a wonderful mother, brother and family. 

I’m so fortunate for genuine friends that love me, encourage me and pray for me; and for the love of those who follow me online - many of you strangers - that root me on and say the kindest things!

God Is Good! 🙏🏽

The last few weeks have been hectic! Shot a U.K. news documentary series and attended events for the White House Correspondents Association weekend.

Also joined the HBCU First Look Film Festival panel at @NorfolkStateUniversity, was invited to the exclusive @visitbmore dinner at @PlatformByJBF; and hosted a gala for @TheLinksInc of Long Island, NY.

Booked and Blessed! 🙏🏽🧳

(Swipe ⬅️ for 📸’s)

I finally got to meet @JanetJackson! When she came on @SherriShowTV I was home sick. 

In addition to having a moment with ‘Miss Jackson if you’re nasty’ at her #TogetherAgainTour stop in NYC, I also had a big laugh about the spelling of my name JAWN with @questlove (all the Philly folks will crack up).

I also met @aliciasilverstone @csiriano & the legendary Ralph Carter aka Michael Evans of “Good Times!” (If you know me, you know I love the classic sitcom “Good Times.”)

#JanetJackson #GoodTimes

Living legends, masters of their craft and people who’ve made an indelible mark on popular culture, thanks to all of the amazing guests that have recently stopped by @SherriShowTV. ✨ #SherriShowTV 

- Swipe ⬅️ for more pics 
- 📸’s by @andrewwerner & @kristenayanah

One thing about living in New York City, you’ll find yourself out in these streets! 

Red carpets, networking mixers,  launch parties, concerts and Broadway shows… let’s just say it’s been a busy few weeks!

#OnlyInNewYork

One thing about @SherriShowTV, we’re going to have great guests; fun conversations; and plenty of laughs!

Thanks to everyone that has stopped by and contributed to our ‘good time’ culture. #SherriShowTV

(Swipe ⬅️ for more pics)

📸’s by @andrewwerner & @kristenayanah

We are in the final stretch of season one of @SherriShowTV and I’m counting down the days until our summer break.

But the guests keep coming through in the meantime and adding to our ‘good time’ vibes! #SherriShowTV

(Swipe ⬅️ for pics)

📸’s @andrewwerner & @kristenayanah

Dear @SherriEShepherd: Thank You for believing that I could bring your vision to life with @SherriShowTV. Thanks for trusting me to help lead this idea of bringing ‘fun, joy and laughter’ back to daytime.

This journey has been God-ordained and I’m so blown away watching Him use you daily to inspire people with humor, heart and your lived-experience.

To our creative team, executive in charge, our technical crew, talent department, integration team, digital team, audience department, security, building staff, glam department, interns and everyone else that had a hand in this debut season: THANK YOU!

I’m so grateful for everyone who encouraged me during season one with your messages of kindness and especially those that kept me lifted in prayer.

Season one is done, but we’re just getting started. 

Love, Jawn Murray
Executive Producer or #SherriShowTV

When @SherriEShepherd asked me take this journey with her at @SherriShowTV, I knew very few Black men had ever been given the opportunity to be an Executive Producer in Daytime TV.

While I’ve had a bunch of Consulting Producer credits to my name, I’d spent most of my career in front of the camera before SHERRI. 

Let’s be honest, while there was so much love and support for what we were doing, there was also (and continues to be) some naysayers.

But I humbly submit to you some stats on our show after season one:

- No. 1 New Show in Daytime
- 2-season renewal of SHERRI
- NAACP Image Award for Outstanding Talk Show
- Bronze Telly Award Winner
- 4 Daytime Emmy Nominations
- Sherri is no. 2 Syndicated Daytime Talk Show in Women 25-54
- Sherri is no. 3 Daytime Talk Show in Women 25-54
- Major Integrations and Advertising Success with Top-Tier Brands
- Critical Acclaim from the Entertainment Industry, Station Affiliates & TV Viewers!

Lastly, SHERRI viewers spent their hard-earned money and literally traveled from all over the world to experience our ‘Good Time’ culture in person! 

Trials and all, this show has been a blessing! And things are only going to get better in season two!

Thank You Sherri Shepherd for believing I could help you bring this vision to life! 

And Thanks to Everyone that genuinely supported year one of this show! 🙏🏽 #SherriShowTV

Swipe ⬅️ for season one memories!

(📸’s 2,5,6,9 & 10 by @andrewwerner)

ATLANTA: Decided to do a last minute trip to Hot 'Lanta to surprise my friend @yannasoulsings who was starring as Effie White in “Dreamgirls” on its closing day.

Got caught up in the insane flight delays and cancelations, so by the time I arrived in The ATL, I felt like I had taken the “Midnight Train to Georgia.”

Not only did my friend Y’Anna Crawley SHINE in “Dreamgirls,” I enjoyed the entire #DreamgirlsATL show (shout-out to @officiallawrenceflowers who crushed as Jame “Thunder” Early!)

Had fun at my friend @absolutelyquad’s pool party, and had a good time catching up with @jpatmanagement at her cookout! 

Laughed with old friends, made some new ones and even spent time with one of my favorites, the legendary songstress @mikithat! 

I packed a lot into a short amount of time… but I can truly say, #Atlanta owes me nothing!

NEW YORK: I’ve been outside in these New York streets enjoying my time off from @SherriShowTV. 

Concerts and cocktails, brunches and premieres; my Hot Boy Summer 🔥 is in full effect! #OnlyInNewYork 🗽

(Swipe ⬅️ for more 📸’s)

Weddings in Kansas City; backyard birthday parties in Philly; hung out in Harlem with @iamanthonyhall; and attended a swanky NYC launch of @drjashton’s magazine.

I’ve been in these streets… Plus, I danced with @MsPattiLaBelle! 

Summer hiatus is in full effect and your boy is enjoying himself!

(Swipe ⬅️ for more 📸 & 🎥)

CINCINNATI: Was definitely a pleasure hosting the @CincyBlackMusicWalkOfFame for the second year in a row. Nearly 5,000 people dressed in all white packed out the Andrew J. Brady Center and at least another 500 sat outside and watched on a monitor as we inducted four dynamic artists.

This is one of my favorite events to host because the crowd is so gracious! This year was extra-special because so many attendees now watch @SherriShowTV and just love what we’re doing.

Got to hang with music legends, see some friends & make some new ones. Not a bad gig!

Thanks to @reecetalk for the invitation & for the work you’re doing in Hamilton County. Thanks also to @tyrhamlindsey + @l.a.i.communications! #Cincinnati 

(Swipe ⬅️ for 📸’s & 🎥)

It’s My Anniversary: I’ve been living in New York City for officially one year now.

Brunches in Harlem and Broadway shows, running these streets with my bros… 

Cocktails with peers, walks on the pier, New York has been good to me this last year! 

Thanks to everyone that’s made this journey a great one so far! 🖤 #ILoveNewYork

(Swipe ⬅️ for more 📸’s)

CHARLESTON, SC: I visited Charleston for the first time to shoot a TV project (I’ll tell you about that later)… and turned a work trip into a vacation.

My friend @mspattilabelle was in town so I went to see her concert. @kardeabrown & @mrsyolandac came and enjoyed the show with me.

I visited the International African American Museum (@iaamuseum); sat on the steps of the Emanuel African Methodist Episcopal Church where the Charleston nine were killed; ate delicious fried oysters; and worked on my suntan. 

Safe to say I had all the feels in Charleston!

(Swipe ⬅️ for 📸’s & 🎥)

Summer hiatus is over and we’re back to work at @SherriShowTV. 

While preparing for our season two premiere on Sept. 18, I couldn’t help but to reflect back on some of the amazing guests that gave us a strong finish to season one.

The ‘Best Time in Daytime’ returns soon, in the meantime enjoy these photos! #SherriShowTV

📸’s by @andrewwerner | Swipe ⬅️ for more pics!

Theme Song by @Trenyce 🎶

So hard to believe the season of summer has come to an end… but the memories will live on because of these friends! 

Like @therealcokoswv sang in the last slide, “If Only You Knew” how much I love everyone I got to hang out with, grab a meal with or just have a good laugh with this summer.

Now, back to life… back to reality!

(Swipe ⬅️ for 📸’s & 🎥)

We’re back with big laughs, more fun, great guests, feel-good moments and plenty of joy!

Thanks to everyone that helped us kick off season two of @SherriShowTV so far! It’s such a privilege to help @sherrieshepherd bring her vision to life! 

And we’re just getting started… #SherriShowTV 

(Swipe ⬅️ for more 📸’s | All shots by @andrewwerner)

Who Wore It Better? This @KidSuper fit that Travis Kelce (@killatrav) rocked while hanging with @TaylorSwift made news and sold out in no time. 

Well, I was able to find it and rocked it on @SherriShowTV! 

Whatcha think? Who wore it better?

PS: Travis appears to be a really cool guy. We’re just having a little fun! 

#TravisKelce #TaylorSwift #KidSuper

Fall came fast and I’m still out in these streets. 

Went to Baltimore to witness @adr1600 & James Ewing get married. Beautiful ceremony!

Then we partied with @DNice during his Club Quarantine Residency at @KennedyCenter in DC. Great concept and awesome mix of talent!

Fun times, memorable moments and always making new friends.

(Swipe ⬅️ for more 📸’s)

JOY: (noun) “The emotion of great delight or happiness caused by something exceptionally good or satisfying; keen pleasure; elation.”

We hope you experience the definition of JOY each time you watch @sherrishowtv! That’s the hope of @SherriEShepherd, me & our entire team!

And THANK YOU to all of the great guests that contribute to our ‘good time’ culture! #SherriShowTV

(Swipe ⬅️ for more 📸’s | All pics by @andrewwerner)

“They talk. We live. Who cares what they say?” — @JayZ on “What We Talkin’ About” from the album “The Blueprint 3.”

I had too much fun attempting to embody Jay-Z for the Halloween show of @SherriShowTV. I think I’m a method actor now. (Time to sign up for @tasha4realsmith’s acting school!)

I don’t know how I let @SherriEShepherd talk me into these crazy things, but if helps folks have a ‘good time,’ then it’s worth it!

Special thanks to @willie_thethird for the look + @tb_hairstylist for the hair.

Kudos to @imjustpatrick_ for leading creative on this episode! 

THANKS to the entire SHERRI staff for the best Halloween show ever! 

#SherriShowTV #Halloween

Trick or Treat? Naw, just EPIC!

The @SherriShowTV homage to Beyoncé’s Renaissance World Tour for Halloween was quite the production!

@SherriEShepherd is a force of nature: 6 wardrobe changes, 2 choreographed dances, had our own Blue Ivy, made gumbo with @KardeaBrown & of course, road a life-sized horse! 

And then I was @JayZ! Lol

THANKS to @MsTinaKnowles for coming through; to @YvetteNoelSchure & @Parkwood for the support; and to @kevinavianceofficial for being the voice of this special episode.

The producers, glam team, production staff, art department and digital team overachieved for this Halloween spectacular! 

The love from the #SherriShowTV viewers has been overwhelming! 🖤🪩

(Swipe ⬅️ for more 📸’s | All images by @andrewwerner)

Sometimes I get talked into doing wackadoo things on @SherriShowTV (the first photo is a great example of that)… But if it keeps bringing joy and laughter to the viewers, I’ll keep saying YES!

Thanks to the amazing guests that have helped make us ‘the best time in daytime,’ and thanks to all of the Sherri Family for our big ratings wins in season two!

(All 📸’s by @andrewwerner | 🎥 by our awesome #SherriShowTV digital team!)

I saw @ReunionTourOfficial in both Newark, NJ and Dallas-Fort Worth, Texas and I have to tell you, if you missed this tour you missed a remarkable experience.

You had @kirkfranklin; The Clark Sisters (@dorindaclarkcole @karenclarksheard  @jackyclarkchisholm & @twinkieclark); @davidandtamela; @israelhoughton & @tyetribbett all on one show!

In Jersey I ran into my friend @cherylpepsii backstage; and in DFW I met @iammiketodd.

Dallas was particularly special because Kirk reunited with God’s Property for the first time in over 20-years.

Always great seeing my friend @ikenice, and @markjphood makes me laugh so hard. Thanks for hanging out with me in DFW @_thatboydorsey! 

If they do this show again, you must see it! #TheReunionTour

They call us “The Best Time in Daytime” and I think our incredible guests contribute to our ‘good time’ culture.

Thanks to all of the great folks that have recently come through @SherriShowTV! 

(Swipe ⬅️ for more 📸 | All shots by @andrewwerner) #SherriShowTV

Tis the season for GRATITUDE! 

The journey of developing and launching @SherriShowTV started with friendship and seeing all that it has become is truly a blessing. And I never take for granted the relationship that @sherrieshepherd and I have.

And this week two other best friends joined our Sherri Family: @Oprah & @GayleKing! (Swipe to see me dance with Gayle!)

And for the first time since we launched, my mom and brother @deon703_ came to visit! Them being here gave me joy!

So appreciative of all the love our #SherriShowTV team received this week (especially from the friends and loved ones who came and sat in the audience)! 

We marked another milestone this week and the elevation of our ‘good time’ culture continues! 🙏🏽🎄💜

(Swipe ⬅️ for 📸 & 🎥 | All photos except slide 8 & 10 by @andrewwerner)

And when we left the @DaytimeEmmys in Los Angeles, we looked like we had a good time! 

Fun times with my @SherriShowTV family, seeing our daytime colleagues & running into a legend or two! 

Thanks to the Emmy-nominated @willie_thethird for helping get my look together! #DaytimeEmmys 

(Swipe for more 📸’s | Slides 2 & 6 by @reyreyfernandez)

It was such a privilege to be able to take my mother to the @WhiteHouse for a holiday reception. I didn’t tell her in advance that she would actually meet President Joe Biden and First Lady Jill Biden. 

(I got to share what the POTUS said to my mom on @SherriShowTV | Swipe right for that 🎥 clip!)

Plus, mom had too much fun hanging out with veteran #WhiteHouse reporter @adr1600 and witnessing so many people tell me how much they love #SherriShowTV

It’s all a blessing! And I am grateful for it! 🙏🏽🎄

Christmas is here and I’m feeling like a champ! Tis the season to be amped! 🎄

Holiday parties kept me on the run; and ugly Christmas sweaters are always so much fun!

Ornaments and eggnog, lights all a glow; waiting to hear Santa Claus say: ‘Ho, Ho, Ho!’ 

Christmas music playing while walking through the mall; the sounds of Mariah, The Temptations and Donny Hathaway give good tidings to us all! 

Family and friends, may your holiday be merry; sending Christmas love from the Executive Producer of “SHERRI!” ♥️

(Swipe for an appearance by Black Santa 🎅🏾 aka @marcoglorious)

When my bestie @SherriEShepherd hosted the Clinton Foundation Gala this year I could tell nervousness had gotten the best of her and she wasn’t enjoying herself. In His perfect timing, God gave me the right words to share with my friend to release her from her anguish and so that she could take in this prestigious opportunity: “YOU BELONG HERE!”
 
As this year comes to an end and many of you are anticipating great things in the coming year, I share this message to inspire you: Stop second-guessing your blessing! No need to play your elevation small! Shake off that imposter syndrome! Be confident in your gifts and abilities!
 
If God has graced you for spaces and allowed you to walk through doors that some could only dream of—appreciate every milestone, be grateful for every level, be present and savor each moment and more than anything always remember: YOU BELONG HERE!
 
Be encouraged as you start your New Year! 🙏🏽

###

Thanks to the @clintonfoundation for the official photos and your hospitality! Swipe ⬅️ for more 📸’s & 🎥!

New Year! 2️⃣4️⃣
Bigger Dreams! 🙏🏽
Greater Goals! 💪🏽
Fresh Vision! 👀

So Much In Store For 2024! 

(I’m a church boy at heart, so you always have to find a rhyme for the new year!)

Happy New Year Fam! 🎉 Swipe ⬅️ for my self-shot 📸’s & 🎥!

“Man cannot discover new oceans unless he has the courage to lose sight of the shore.” – André Gide

Solo vacation to The Bahamas!
